President Joseph R. Biden hosted a conference call with Allies and partners to discuss their unified response to Russia's war on Ukraine. They recognized the bravery of the Ukrainian people and discussed their continued support in terms of security, economic, and humanitarian assistance. The leaders also discussed their coordinated efforts to hold Russia accountable and impose severe costs and consequences. They emphasized the importance of maintaining global economic stability, particularly in relation to energy prices. The call included participants such as Prime Minister Trudeau of Canada, European Commission President von der Leyen, President Macron of France, Chancellor Scholz of Germany, and Prime Minister Johnson of the United Kingdom.